This year has been an absolute blessing! 🌟 We are over the moon with the response our little blue bottle has received within a year of launching. 🥰

But we're only getting started. We have so much more in store for you in the upcoming year and we can't wait to share it with you! 2022 - Can you start already?! 🤷🏻‍♀️
If you could turn back time, what would you change about this year? ⌛

🌀NEW PRODUCT LAUNCH UPDATE🌀
Hi d’you fam! Shamika here. I thought it was about time that we give you an honest low down on our upcoming product launch. I am consciously aware how patient you guys have been and how eager you all are for our new launch. I’m just as eager but sometimes reality slows us down. So here’s what up:

1️⃣ We’ve spent all of the last 12 months perfecting this formula to get you something unique. We take longer in our R&D because we also order with high MOQs. With higher MOQs is higher risk, which means we cannot launch an almost-perfect formula. We can ONLY launch an absolutely perfect and 100% satisfactory formula. With smaller MOQs there is room for mitigating errors, which we don’t have. We spend longer time testing the formula internally and only when we are a fully satisfied that this is the best version possible with this particular formula and that particular packaging is when we go into mass production. So the time taken to perfect the formula is longer than with other brands.

2️⃣ With the pandemic the global supply chain has been severely impacted. That means not only are our production schedules jam packed, so are our shipping containers and ingredient supply schedules from each individual supplier. It took us a long time to source this 1 ingredient in the formulation because only a couple of suppliers globally have this ingredient. 

3️⃣ Our packaging sampling & approvals took far longer to approve this time than before because our team could not travel on site to South Korea. SK has still not opened up visas to any foreign nationals. Every small change in colour injection, or font size or font colour means a new sample has to be made, shipped to us in India and physically approved before it goes into mass production. Even after the packaging got approved our manufacturer schedules have been so blocked out that scheduling a day for our mass production has been a fight🥵

4️⃣ Simultaneous to all this we have to get our licensing and registration procedure done in both countries South Korea and India before we launch the product.

5️⃣ WHERE WE STAND TODAY: See rest in comments below👇🏻
My secret super-power wish is to be able to float on clouds ☁️☁️. What's yours?

latestPosts.caption:
I am NOT a lip girlie. I’m not someone who hoards lip balms, chapsticks, lipsticks or that girl who can’t wait to get the latest lip stain. I’m someone who wants to feel NOTHING on my lips, and I don’t care to reapply much on my lips either. 

And I’m working on more than a few lip formulas at the moment🙈. So naturally I’m focused on creating textures that ~feel like nothing~ yet do everything as expected. Lip nectar was exactly that. It’s a lightweight formula that will absolutely not sit on your lips. It was designed to get the job done and disappear. It will soften the driest lips and then vanish. It’ll heal severely cracked lips within minutes (no jokes) and then softy make its presence thin. This was intentional. 

The aim of a lip balm is to heal dry lips. But with thicker balms that sit on your skin, our mind gets accustomed to want to keep having that feeling. Ever heard of the reverse phenomenon where the more you apply the drier your lips feel without it? It’s not that your lips are actually getting drier without the lip balm, it’s just that your baseline has changed, and your mind is now used to feeling a coat of something sitting on your lips - so bare lips without anything even in their normal natural state start to feel dry. This is just cognitive bias, not an actual hydration problem. 

With lip nectar we wanted to create a formula that heals without being loud. The in-between texture of lip nectar does exactly that - it’s quiet & effortless in its presence, it dutifully does its job of healing, it doesn’t leave behind a streak of wax, and you’ll just naturally find your lips softened without needing to reapply it too often.

Those that prefer thicker lip balms - fair play this may not be your new love :) 
As for me, I’m slowly converting to a lip girlie since we are developing so many new lip formulas👀
Do you like minimalist / effortless formulas? Or are you a long-wear, bold lip girlie? What would you like to see from us in lip textures next?
